rComments: Without a doubt the best prof I have had at U of T. Genuinely cared about students. Really fair grader. Course material challenging but interesting. Very approachable.
An easy course (very simple midterm questions - short answer).  BUT beware the negative marking scheme for the final (with multiple choice)

I thought her lectures were pretty clear and the assignments actually make it easier to understand the methodology used in neurobio. However, the TAs mark weird and she can sometimes come off rude.The course was not as easy as it may seem at first.
lots of memorization.. LOTS! as much work needed as for psychology.
great prof. i hope she continues teaching the course for many years to come
